content:
@OJ everything Matt said is completely right. Also,

> If you wrote 1000 songs and then just put songs 1001-1010 out onto the internet, people will find you quickly because the songs will be great. I promise you.

It's also worth noting that you *might* get lucky with song 100, or song 10, or even song 1. But if you haven't put in the reps and get caught up in your own hype, you'll have a hard time following up that initial success and all the social media followers in the world will mean nothing when your subsequent releases flop.
